<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="257" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1471,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">
Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Mielke, C. G. C. &amp; Basu, D. N. &amp; Pawar, U. &amp; Ismavel, V. A. &amp; Rawlins, J. E. &amp; Kunte, K." box="[219,442,1580,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref8927" refString="Grehan, J. R., Mielke, C. G. C., Basu, D. N., Pawar, U., Ismavel, V. A., Rawlins, J. E. &amp; Kunte, K. (2022) A new species of Endoclita C. &amp; R. Felder, 1874 ghost moth from Karimganj district of Assam, India, with comments on the genus in Northeastern India, and clarification of E. signifer (Walker, 1856) (Lepidoptera: Hepialidae). ZooNova, 16, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="2022">
Grehan 
<emphasis box="[307,355,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">et al</emphasis>
. (2022)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<collectingRegion box="[570,646,1580,1606]" country="India" name="Assam" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">Assam</collectingRegion>
as its distribution. However, Khasia Hills was part of 
<collectingRegion box="[1238,1314,1580,1606]" country="India" name="Assam" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">Assam</collectingRegion>
before 21 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1425,1436,1580,1594]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">st</superScript>
January, 1972, and after that is part of 
<collectingRegion box="[628,756,1616,1642]" country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
. So, the distribution has been corrected accordingly.
</paragraph>
